<br>
Is there a limit on the delay of a weapon and how does it work. If I had a weapon that the delay was 18, would a 75% haste help me just as much as 100%? I figure there is an equation that shows how much the delay per point decreases on the increase of a certain % of haste. Also is there a limit that you can't go beyond. I understand the limits on haste but the delay of a weapon is different.<br>
<br>
For instance.<br>
IF 10% haste = 1 point of delay decreased <br>
THEN a weapon with a normal delay of 18 would actually have a delay of 8 with 100% haste.<br>
<br>
                     OR<br>
<br>
IF 5% haste = 1 point of delay decreased<br>
THEN a weapon with a normal delay of 18 would actually have a delay of -2 with 100% haste. Is that even possible?<br>
<br>
I hope I made sense. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=beornegarfrostwolf>Beornegar Frostwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/11/03 1:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3139.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapon Delays and Haste</span><hr size=1> If I remember correctly, at one time the general consensus was that the effective delay of a weapon couldnt get below 10.  Not sure if that's still true or not, but I've never heard anyone say otherwise....and I don't remember what the equation for calculating delay based on haste, but the numbers in your post are way off....somebody that knows how the equation works post something to enlighten us please. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
