<br>
Hasted Weapon delay = Weapon delay/(1 + haste%/100))<br>
<br>
In this case, an 18 delay weapon at 100% haste would have a 9 delay.<br>
<br>
There was a weapon that dropped in the game with a delay of 6 so I am guessing that there isn't really a lower limit on delay.  It was a pal or sk weapon with 2 damage and a 6 delay.  (name had something to do with a bixie stinger iirc)<br>
<br>
I am guessing that people &quot;believed&quot; there was due to the way the parsers/logs work.  The clock goes by seconds and therefore the log listings for damage occur on the even second implying a 10 delay minimum.  If you were careful you would probably find that you attacked more times than possible on a given second from parses if you subscribe to the 10 delay min theory and had a sufficiently fast weapon and high enough haste.  (although this is speculation on my part)  It would help to have different types of weapons in each hand too to distinguish between them, ie 1hb (you crush) and 1hs (you slash).<br>
<br>
